## PHP Arrays (Indexed & Associative)

1) Indexed Array
--> Uses numbers (0,1,2...)
--> Stores values in order

2) Associative Array

--> Uses key → value pairs
--> Custom keys instead of index

## Example

<?php
// Indexed Array
$fruits = array("Apple", "Mango", "Banana");
echo $fruits[1];        // Mango

// Associative Array
$marks = array("Maths"=>90, "Science"=>80);
echo $marks["Maths"];           // 90
?